            <item>
                <title>Let&#39;s implement &#39;Stack&#39; in Python</title>
                <link>https://alexkval.github.io/posts/stack-in-python/</link>
                <guid isPermaLink="true">https://alexkval.github.io/posts/stack-in-python/</guid>
                <pubDate>Fri, 10 Jul 2020 22:16:18 &#43;0100</pubDate>
                
                    <author>alexkval@gmail.com (Alexander Shemetovskiy)</author>
                
                <copyright>Copyright ¬© Alexander Shemetovskiy</copyright>
                <description>&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-py&#34; data-lang=&#34;py&#34;&gt;a &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; Stack()     &lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# []&lt;/span&gt;
a&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;push(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;one&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;)   &lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# [&amp;#39;one&amp;#39;]&lt;/span&gt;
a&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;push(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;two&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;)   &lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# [&amp;#39;one&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;two&amp;#39;]&lt;/span&gt;
a&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;top()         &lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# &amp;#39;two&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
a&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;push(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;three&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# [&amp;#39;one&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;two&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;three&amp;#39;]&lt;/span&gt;
a&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;top()         &lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# &amp;#39;three&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
a&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;size()        &lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# 3&lt;/span&gt;
a&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;pop()         &lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# &amp;#39;three&amp;#39;  [&amp;#39;one&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;two&amp;#39;]&lt;/span&gt;
a&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;pop()         &lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# &amp;#39;two&amp;#39;    [&amp;#39;one&amp;#39;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is the API I want to have for the &amp;lsquo;Stack&amp;rsquo; data structure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let&amp;rsquo;s implement it in &lt;code&gt;Python&lt;/code&gt; step by step.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                
                
                
                
                
                    
                        
                            
                                
                                
                                
